        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="547"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <head>547. Telegram 1658 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d547fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/3–2156.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-21"
                            >March 21, 1956, 7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d547-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d547-1"/>
                <p>1658. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Concur Clough’s memo to <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName> March
                    12 that not rpt not desirable ARC attempt by letter seek assistance CHICOM Red
                    Cross release 13. Nicholson should however utilize all possibilities at May
                    meeting to impress on CHICOM Red Cross American concern continued detention
                    13.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
